RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 1 1M Turf CR: 70. Maiden Special Weight Purse 27000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE, FOUR, AND FIVE YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. (If management deems it inadvisable to run this race on the Turf, it will be run at a distance of 1 Mile on the main track.) (Rail at 15 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MIZ CALI raced in the two path around the first turn, chased the leader on the outside up the backstretch, took over while saving ground around the far turn and held clear to the finish. PRINCESS OF MALIBU hit the gate leaving it, stalked the pace setter on the outside around the first turn and up the backstretch, continued around the far turn in the two path and chased the winner home in the lane. HIGHLY CREATIVE saved ground early, raced in the middle of the pack on the inside up the backstretch, continued around the far turn in the two path and finished evenly. PAT'S GAL saved ground around the first turn, led the way on the inside up the backstretch, dropped back while saving ground around the far bend and continued to tire in the stretch. ROLL GYPSY ROLL saved ground around the first turn, trailed the field up the backstretch, came around the far turn in the two and three path and was empty from there.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 2 1M Dirt CR: 85. Claiming Purse 11000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR MINNESOTA BRED WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES OR WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE JANUARY 3. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At One Mile Or Over Since June 3 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000 (Claiming Races For $4,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility). Minnesota Bred Claiming Price $7,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CLUB MESQUITE saved ground early, trailed the field up the backstretch, swung out to the four path to began a bid coming around the far bend and drew off in the lane. UNLEASH THE BEAST raced in the three path early, dueled on the outside up the backstretch, continued to battle from the three path coming around the far turn, was caught in upper stretch and chased the winner home from there. HIGHTAIL COWBOY dueled on the inside around the first turn and up the backstretch, continued to battle from the rail coming around the second turn and gave way in the final furlong. SMART CALL raced in the two path early, continued up the backstretch in the middle of the pack on the inside, saved ground around the far bend and showed no kick. DILLON ROCKS raced in the middle of the pack on the outside through the opening half mile, continued around the far turn in the three path and made no bid. NIETZSCHE raced in the two path around the first turn, continued up the backstretch off the pace, dropped back while saving ground around the second turn and was empty in the stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 3 1M Turf CR: 87. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 28000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, TRIAL OR STATE BRED ALLOWANCE OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $16,000. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-w inners Of A Race Since June 3 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000. Minnesota Bred Claiming Price $25,000. (If management deems it inadvisable to run this race on the Turf, it will be run at a distance of 1 Mile on the main track.) (Rail at 15 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SWANAGE led the way while saving ground around the first turn, dueled on the inside up the backstretch, continued to battle from the two path coming around the far turn and dug in gamely in the lane to just hold the win. ROLLIN BLACKOUT bumped with the horse to her outside leaving the gate, saved ground around the first turn, chased the leaders on the inside up the backstretch, continued around the far bend in the two path, began a bid approaching the quarter pole and gained ground late too narrowly miss. DREAMING BIZ raced in the two path early, settled in the middle of the pack for the run up the backstretch, saved ground around the second bend, launched a bid in upper stretch and gained ground late. FAST TO FORTUNE raced in the two path around the first bend, pressed the pace on the outside up the backstretch, dueled from the three path around the far turn and weakened in the final furlong. MERLIN'S SISTER bumped with the horse to her outside leaving the gate, saved ground through the opening quarter, raced off the pace coming up the backstretch, continued to save ground around the far turn and never threatened. A THOUSAND DREAMS bumped with the horses to both sides at the start, saved ground early, stalked the pace setters on the outside up the backstretch, continued around the far turn in the two path and tired in the lane. NAUGHTY NELLIE trailed the field the entire way around the oval, saved ground throughout and was never a factor.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 4 5F Turf CR: 92. Claiming Purse 13000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES SINCE JANUARY 3 OR WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE APRIL 23 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $7,500 (Claiming Races For $6,250 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility). Minnesota Bred Claiming Price $12,500. (If management deems it inadvisable to run this race on the Turf, it will be run at a distance of 5 Furlongs on the main track.) (Rail at 15 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: A ROZE AND WINE broke sharply and was sent to an early lead, continued to show the way while saving ground around the turn and held clear while drifting in the stretch. MR NAVIGATOR tracked the pace setter on the inside through the opening quarter of a mile, saved ground around the turn and kept on to the wire. SAMURAI MIKE raced in the middle of the pack on the inside early, saved ground around the bend and improved position in the lane. LONELY PRIVATE chased the frontrunner between horses up the backstretch, navigated the turn from the two path and was outkicked in the stretch. PERFECT FANNY raced in the middle of the pack on the outside through the opening stages, came around the turn in the two and three path and tired from there. GIANT GAMBLE raced off the pace up the backstretch, came around the turn in the two path and made no bid.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 5 1M Dirt CR: 72. Maiden Special Weight Purse 31000. FOR MN-BRED MAIDENS, THREE, FOUR, AND FIVE YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WIN OVER WYATT saved ground around the first turn, led the way on the inside up the backstretch, continued to save ground around the far turn, kicked clear in upper stretch and just held the win. RAMBLINGAMBLINMAN saved ground early, tracked the leader on the inside up the backstretch, continued to save ground around the far bend, began a bid entering the stretch and gained ground late to the wire to narrowly miss. GOING AT IT floated out to the three path around the first turn, chased the pace setter between horses up the backstretch, challenged from the two path coming around the far turn and was outkicked in the lane. CAUSEWAY SURPISE raced in the five path around the first turn, settled off the pace on the outside for the run up the backstretch, came around the second bend in the two path and never threatened. KAL EL raced in the four path early, stalked the leader on the outside up the backstretch, came around the far turn in the three path and flattened out in the stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 6 1M Turf CR: 96. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 28000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, TRIAL OR STATE BRED ALLOWANCE OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $16,000. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Si nce June 3 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000. Minnesota Bred Claiming Price $25,000. (If management deems it inadvisable to run this race on the Turf, it will be run at a distance of 1 Mile on the main track.) (Rail at 15 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: INESPERADO bumped with LORING PARK in the first couple of strides, saved ground around the first turn, chased the leaders on the inside up the backstretch, continued to save ground around the far bend, switched to the outside to began a bid entering the stretch and dueled to the wire while drifting mildly late to just hold the win. TWOKO BAY raced off the pace on the outside through the opening half mile, continued around the far bend in the four path, launched a bid approaching the quarter pole and gained ground late to just miss. LORING PARK raced in tight quarters and bumped with INESPERADO the first time by, came around the first bend in the two path, tracked the leaders on the outside up the backstretch, began a bid from the two path coming around the turn and kept on to the finish. BOB'S ALL IN raced in the two path early, settled off the pace between horses for the run up the backstretch, navigated the second bend from the three path and improved position in late stretch. COASTAL WATERS raced off the pace on the inside around the first turn and up the backstretch, continued to save ground around the far turn and showed no kick. KID'S INHERITANCE bumped with the horse to his outside at the start, recovered to lead the field from the two path around the first turn, continued to show the way on the inside up the backstretch, dueled from the rail around the far turn and in upper stretch and weakened in the final furlong. ASTRONOMICAL bumped with the horse to his inside leaving the gate, raced in the three path early, pressed the pace on the outside up the backstretch, dropped back while racing in the three path around the far bend and continued to fade in the stretch.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: BODENHEIMER led the way up the backstretch, saved ground around the turn and drew off in the lane. SHIP IT RED raced off the pace on the outside early, came around the turn in the three path, began a bid passing the quarter pole and gained ground in the stretch but was no match for the winner. EUROMANTIC tracked the pace setter on the outside up the backstretch, came around the bend in the two path and finished evenly. MARK THE MOOSE raced off the pace on the inside through the opening quarter of a mile, saved ground around the turn and made no bid. BLAME J D chased the leader on the inside up the backstretch, saved ground around the bend and tired in the lane.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 8 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 96. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 15000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $5,000 (MINNESOTA BRED $7,500) OR LESS IN 2022 - 2023 OR CLAIMING PRICE $10,000. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. RACE.FOOTNOTES: MR. WHO chased the leader on the outside up the backstretch, began a bid from the three path coming around the turn and kicked clear in the final furlong. OPTIMAL COURAGE dueled on the outside through the opening quarter of a mile, continued to battle from the two path around the far turn and in upper stretch and chased the winner home late. SINGLE ME OUT raced off the pace early, navigated the turn from the three path and improved position mildly in the stretch. STORMIN HONGKONG trailed the field up the backstretch, saved ground around the bend and showed no kick. CANNONBALL COMIN dueled on the inside up the backstretch, dropped back while saving ground around the turn and continued to tire from there.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 9 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 108. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 29500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON $20,000 TWICE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR STATE BRED SINCE JANUARY 3 OR WHICH HAVE NOT WON $20,000 ONCE SINCE APRIL 3 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR STATE BRED OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $35,000. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since June 3 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $35,000. Minnesota Bred Claiming Price $50,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DOCTOR OSCAR was sent to an early lead racing up the backstretch, saved ground around the turn and drew off in the lane, much the best. HOLDEN THE LUTE raced off the pace on the inside early, began a bid from the two path coming around the turn and kept on in the lane while proving to be no match for the winner. MINISTER OF SOUL chased the pace setter on the inside up the backstretch, came around the turn in the two path and finished evenly. DEFLATER trailed the field through the opening quarter, saved ground around the bend and showed no kick. CENTRAL PARK tracked the leader on the outside up the backstretch, navigated the turn from the three path and faded in the stretch. CITRUS BAY raced off the pace on the outside through the opening stages, continued around the turn in the two path and was empty in the lane.
